1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,730
Much lack of self-confidence can be traced directly to a mismanaged memory.

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:09,009
Your brain is very much like a bank.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:13,170
Every day you make thought deposits in your mind bank.

4
00:00:13,440 --> 00:00:16,930
These thought deposits grow and become your memory.

5
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:23,170
When you settle down to think or when you face a problem, in effect you say to your memory bank,

6
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:25,889
what do I already know about this?

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:36,050
Your memory bank automatically answers and supplies you with bits of information relating to the situation that you deposited on previous occasions.

8
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:42,050
Your memory, then, is the basic supplier of raw material for your new thought.

9
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:46,370
The teller in your memory bank is tremendously reliable.

10
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,129
He never crosses you up.

11
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:54,930
If you approach him and say, Mr. Teller, let me withdraw some thoughts I'd deposited in the past,

12
00:00:55,120 --> 00:01:00,450
proving I'm inferior to just about everybody else, he'll say, Certainly,

13
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:00,930
sir.

14
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:05,249
Recall how you failed two times previously when you tried this?

15
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:10,610
Recall what your sixth grade teacher told you about your inability to accomplish things?

16
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:14,930
Recall what you overheard some fellow workers saying about you?

17
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:24,050
Recall And on and on, Mr. Teller goes, digging out of your brain thought after thought that proves you are inadequate.

18
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,290
But suppose you visit your memory teller with this request.

19
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:31,730
Mr. Teller, I face a difficult decision.

20
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:35,889
Can you supply me with any thoughts which will give me reassurance?

21
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:39,970
And again, Mr. Teller says, certainly, sir.

22
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:46,370
But this time, he delivers thoughts you deposited earlier that say you can succeed.

23
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:51,170
Recall the excellent job you did in a similar situation before?

24
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:54,850
Recall how much confidence Mr. Smith placed in you?

25
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:57,889
Recall what your good friends said about you?

26
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,649
Recall...

27
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:05,810
Mr. Teller, perfectly responsive, lets you withdraw the thought deposits you want to withdraw.

28
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,370
After all, it is your bank.

